rComments: See, now this is what a prof should be - inspirational, fair, ethical, demanding that her students read, a multidimensional thinker among just a few attributes. This is your tuition and tax dollars well spent! Take her small seminars and ignore the deadwood big HIS classes.

Professor Neimenis was good professor. Her lectures were thought provoking. However, I felt that this course did not need to be a full year course as it was very repetitive. At times it was also very abstract. However, tutorials were very helpful in clarifying concepts.

Michelle Murphy was hands down the best prof I have ever had. She is a genius, her lectures are brilliantly argued and extremely well organized. She will ask you to do a lot of reading, but you will learn tonnes. I have used things she first taught me in NEW classes as well as HIS class over and over throughout my academic career. TAKE HER CLASS

great professor! down to earth, approachable and friendly, clear lecturer, very knowledgeable, amazing material! interested in her students and wants u to do well... quite cute as well!

intelligent and enthusiastic professor who makes the material accessible to everyone and easy to understand. a bit unapproachable and a hard marker though.
i LOVED this class and this prof.  my friend didn't like her or the class.  the tutorials weren't very useful, but the material was really meaningful.
great material, good lectures.  she sometimes went to fast, but slowed down after some complaints.  i liked her a lot.
